## When to use
Use this skill when you need to monitor I/O operations and system resource usage in detail for performance analysis or troubleshooting.

## Approach
Utilize the `shell_exec` tool to run the `iostat` command with advanced options, such as `-d -x`, which provides detailed information on device statistics and extended device statistics. This allows for a deeper insight into disk I/O operations and system load.

## Example
To monitor system resource usage with detailed I/O statistics every 2 seconds, use:
```shell
shell_exec("iostat -dx 2")
```

## Pitfalls
Ensure that the `iostat` command is available on your system. If monitoring for extended periods, be aware of the impact of frequent polling on system performance.